title: For Sale:  M1898 Krag-Jorgensen
postcontent:
So it's an 1898 model,made in 1901 based on the serial number
Has the M1902 rear sight with windage adjustment and neat little flip up peep sight

I'm no gunsmith,but heres what I consider an overly critical description of condition-

Has very little blue left,but most collectors prefer that over refinished.
Action and mechanicals are smooth as butter,as these are known to be.
Rifling is deep,looks great,to me.
Doesnt have pitting,frosty to dull shiny bore (I have yet to even clean this rifle)
My problem with this rifle is the stock.It was customized LONG ago,by sanding out the finger grooves and recontouring the buttstock (Which actually makes it a very comfortable grip,just not "correct")
Has a neat old WW1 era "A" company infantry badge embedded in the butt

If I were a hunter,or if I could afford an original military stock,I would keep this rifle.
I have 1 brand new box of Remington 180 grain Core Lokt that goes with it.
I am selling for less than I paid 3 weeks ago. $225 cash takes it!
Or will trade for other Military rifles or handguns.

I bought this gun for everyday carry and competition shooting, and no question about it, I immediately fell in love with it. After I had the upgrades put in it, it became my pride and joy. Sadly, I am needing to sell it because I need money to pay for my last semester of school out of pocket. I work at one of the largest gun ranges/firearms stores in the Mid-south, so you can rest assured that this gun has been professionally cared for and pampered. 

I am 100% confident that this gun will sell itself without me writing an essay on it. If you know anything at all about CZ’s, then you know who Cajun Gun Works (CGW) is, and how superb their quality parts are and how phenomenal their upgrades make stock a CZ. The Pro-package is the top tier option at CGW, and you can read up on what all they do in this package at cajungunworks.com. So, I really don’t know what else to say about this amazing piece, other than just give you the facts on what you’re bidding on: 

-	Firearm has had the CGW Pro-package upgrades installed and internals polished to mirror finish
-	Pistol has also had the Flat Mainspring Plug (replaces OEM lanyard loop) and the Flat Mag Brake from CZ Custom installed (so CZ mags free fall)
-	8.4lbs DA trigger pull (very short pull thanks to CGW), and 3.4lbs SA trigger break - tested with electronic trigger scale
-	Incredibly short trigger reset (again, thanks to CGW upgrades!)
-	Gun has had only about 800 rounds put through it (approx. 400 before and 400 after the CGW work)
- Firearm is in overall near-mint condition

-	Comes with 2x MecGar 17rd mags (flush frame fit) and the 2x OEM 18rd extended CZ SP-01 mags
-	Comes with Fobos Roto-paddle kydex holster
-	Comes with spare CGW 13# recoil spring
-	Comes with CGW sear cage slave pin, and CGW starter punch for tapping out pins for future work
-	Comes with all OEM parts that were upgraded/replaced
-	This gun will out-shoot all but the most accurate shooters on the planet at extreme pistol distances, and the recoil is next to nothing. You just have to shoot one to believe it!

title: For Sale:  BNIB HK USP .40 S&W Variant 1
postcontent:
Stop in and see us at Deadwood Guns and Ammo in Carlisle, Ohio for all your shooting and archery needs.

From the HK site:
Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters.

Features:
Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame
Polygonal bore profile for increased velocity, easier cleaning, and longer barrel life
Can be converted to any of nine trigger firing modes
Corrosion resistant “Hostile Environment” blued finish
From the HK Site:
Oversized trigger guard for use with gloves
One piece machined slide made from nitro-carburized steel
Universal mounting grooves for installing accessories
Ambidextrous magazine release lever
Extended slide release
Patented Lock-Out Safety device

title: For Sale:  Bowtech Diamond edge youth bow
postcontent:
This is the perfect beginner bow. Left hand. Draw weight 30-40 lbs. 3 point hostage captive rest. 3 pin fiber optic sight. 3 arrow quiver and 3 carbon arrows. wrist sling.  peep sight. matching blue string loop. This is a youth bow but would work perfect for a kid or even a lady. My 14 year old son shot 2" groups at Gander Mountain last Thursday. This bow is pretty darn accurate. We were shooting a at a superball for fun and he hit it just as many times as I did. Perfect time to get practice and a head start on the upcoming archery season.
 Asking $200. Any questions call Scott REDACTED 

 Bowhunting.net review
 For a youth or novice bow, the Edge surpasses all I've looked at. Most of your beginner bows on the market are made from poured Magnesium, which is heavy especially for a youth shooter. The Edge is molded from 6061 aluminum. That in combination with the carbon limbs only weighs 3.3 lbs. The brace height on this bow 6 ¾" and the bow is 32 1/2 " axle to axle. The shorter bow with a large brace height ensures that it will be forgiving with a small frame shooter. To tell you the truth, this bow is manufactured with as much quality as the Diamond Liberty. 

 The Edge is a dual cam bow. Now here is the awesome thing on this. This bow is just not a bow that you buy and your child outgrows it within a year or so. The Edge has an adjustable draw length of 18 to 28". This way the bow can grow with your child. There is no need for a bow press to change the draw length on it either, which will save you money and time from running to a local pro-shop to get it adjusted.
